comments.body:
@seberg, this is admittedly a "quick and dirty" implementation (where "quick" refers to implementation time, not execution time).  Is there an existing pattern in the NumPy API for treating an n-d array (with arbitrary strides) as a 1-d array that would better here?  I can implement *something*, but it would be great if there is already a nice way to do it.

@bashtage, yes, with `axis=None`, a fast path for the contiguous case (either C- or F-, actually) should be pretty easy.

@eric-wieser, I've tested it using arrays with various strides, and it has worked, but maybe I'm just blind to an obvious counter-example.  Are there specific tests you think would be good to check?

